\id MRK - Nakara portions 
\h Mark 
\toc1 Mark 
\toc2 Mark 
\toc3 Mark 
\mt1 Mark  
\c 4
\s1  
\r  
\p
\v 35 Wurdamayena nina Djisas wakana baberrawa djawirna. “Ngurrbidjeba kanawa belbaya ngakaliyarra.”  
\v 36 Karr-bakorrawa banabawana nina djawirna bakaya Djisas kana kabbala yingawa narr-munga kabbala bakakaya bardayika.   
\p
\v 37 Nadjorra wunamirla djaba balbala wunamirla nayaka. Kuka bonganjana kana kabbala. Kabbala mankirdiyana.  
\v 38 Djisas yurda kana kabbala bila belbana yurda. Djawirna bakulkiya bawakana liyawa, “Djabba, nangarda njeyaba njeyurda? Njeyaba korla keydjama anjekarkaya nguberrabba. Nguberrabba korlaba ngubumarnkirriya.”   
\p
\v 39 Djisas karamarda wakana lorr balbala kuka, “Baddiyana, marawaka!” Kanaba yingawa balbala baddiyana maburlarr nina.   
\p
\v 40 Djisas wakana baberrawa djawirna “Nangarda liyawa njeyaba njawarakuma liyawa balbala? Ngarabba ngakadjawiya kendjarra. Korla nganakalewa ngarabba?   
\p
\v 41 Bawakana baberrawa kanawa nguyawa “Kara njinka wunakelaya? Nangarda liyawa balbala yingawa baddiyana nguburrkeleya liyawa nakabba?” Baberrabba kunara balilibeyana liyawa bawar-kumada liyawa.   
\c 16
\s1  
\p
\v 2 Barramarngada nina Sunday, nabbena kididjana. Kawarr-kakardabba ngardawa-niya nawara barribana kana wunaddakala. Ba-berrabba barribana beneya Djisas. Barawabba Djisas djormarda. Nawara yinmiya Mary Magdalene, kunjma Salomi, mubba Mary yinmiya mangaya James.  
\v 3 Ba-berrabba ba-diyaka, ba-wakana ba-berrama, “Nginka wunaddakala wunamila yakaka mardda ngu-berraba ngu-bidjeba kana mera wunaddakala?”   
\p
\v 4 Nawara bokkolarna, ba-nana wunaddakala warranbiyana.   
\p
\v 5 Ba-berrabba ba-bonganjana wunaddakala. Ba-nana wunakelaya nina kana nakkayel. Na-kabba nebbeya karrbardana kakaya. Kunara balilibeyana.  
\v 6 Na-kabba wakana ba-berrawa, “Korla nganjawarakuma. Nu-berrabba ngangada ngurrbadjarrakindja? Na-kabba Djisas kana na-keyniya Nazareth. Na-kabba ba-burda Djisas kardanjayana yuna. Djisas na-kabba karamarda. Na-kabba korla kakkana. Na. Neyana kana ba-bangiya wunaddakala. Korla na-kabba kakkana.”   